Title: Merry Monster Survey
Description: Watch videos and answer questions to learn new words (60-75 minutes)!
Answer.Comments: You said to describe any changes I noticed in the videos. At first, every word worked the same way: I watched a video demonstrating it, then guessed whether it was in two videos, then watched three more training videos, then guessed on two more. About halfway through the experiment, the second two stages disappeared, so that for each word I was only watching one training video and making two guesses.

Title: Merry Monster Survey
Description: Watch videos and answer questions to learn new words (60-75 minutes)!
Answer.Comments:
Overall, I thought this experiment was well put together.  However, I would suggest giving the user the option to skip the "Let's see it again" video replays.  Also, the question regarding the plus sign was a bit receptive.  I assume you were trying to asses if the survey participant saw the entire video clip. 

I would suggest placing all three of the examples of the verb for questions 1 - 10 on one screen rather than three separate screens with replays.

Title: Merry Monster Survey
Description: Watch videos and answer questions to learn new words (60-75 minutes)!
Answer.Comments: Those red plus signs were obnoxious and distracting. If they are an attention check, maybe you could have people hit a button or click when they see the plus sign instead of a "yes" or "no." I was trying to focus on whether or not I saw the verb, and I would often get derailed by clicking that other "yes" or "no" first. One time, it actually skipped the screen before I could click "yes," so that was strange. I didn't mind the number ordering. That was a different task between videos, so it wasn't frustrating.
